# WaspsWithBazookas

Distributed load testing tool built in Rust. Think of it as having an army of angry wasps, each armed with rocket launchers, ready to absolutely *obliterate* your servers with HTTP requests.

## Features

- **Distributed Power**: Coordinate wasps across multiple servers
- **High Performance**: Rust-powered with wrk backend
- **Easy to Use**: Simple CLI and REST API
- **Production Ready**: Health checks, graceful shutdown, comprehensive logging

## Quick Start

```powershell
# Start the hive (command center)
hive --port 4269

# Start a wasp
wasp --hive-url http://localhost:4269 --port 3001

# Start test dummy server
test-dummy --port 8080

# Launch an attack!
curl -X PUT http://localhost:4269/hive/poke -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"target": "http://localhost:8080", "t": 10, "c": 100, "d": 30}'
```

## Components

- **Hive**: Command center for coordinating wasps
- **Wasp**: Individual load testing agents
- **Test Dummy**: Ultra-fast httpbin-style test server

For more information, visit: https://github.com/Phara0h/WaspsWithBazookas
